column5: Looks like Dryden is getting Hammered ! Time to go Skidoing !
Gonna need the augers may 20,and tip ups.
Gonna need this today.Good thing I put my plow back on.Still snowing and blowing hard.Seems like 5" or so.
You gonna use that cooker today???the one next to your wheeler.
Ha! We are getting a few flakes today here in good ol' Ioway! 33 degrees this morning. Covered emerging flowers with towels last night. Lawn is fertilized and mower is ready!!! Bill

Snow stopped last evening.Wind has gone away this morning.Sun has come out this morning.Theres a couple of us planning to go ice fishing Sunday and Monday.lol.Fairly late for ice fishing.Last year I had my boat in Cliff Lake on 26 th.Weather will warm a bit in daytime but nights still go below 0/32f all week.One month till opener.Looking like a tight schedule.Wife and I always enjoyed the open water prior to opener
You may have to winterize that lawn mower and put it back into hibernation again,,,,,snowing in Rochester now!!
